1
00:00:28,666 --> 00:00:34,083
[organ music]

2
00:00:34,166 --> 00:00:36,125
[organ continues]

3
00:00:47,541 --> 00:00:48,916
[AKARI]
Quiet, please.

4
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,166
If you're ready,

5
00:00:50,250 --> 00:00:52,916
we shall begin the
exchange of vows ceremony.

6
00:00:54,541 --> 00:00:56,041
[AKARI]
Kirin Shima.

7
00:00:56,125 --> 00:00:58,791
Do you take this woman
to be your mentor?

8
00:00:58,875 --> 00:01:03,166
Do you vow to love her as
long as you both shall live?

9
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:04,500
[KIRIN]
I do!

10
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,541
[AKARI]
And do you, Raika Hino,

11
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:10,125
take this woman
to be your Amica?

12
00:01:10,208 --> 00:01:14,541
And do you, too, vow to love her
as long as you both shall live?

13
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:16,333
[RAIKA]
I do.

14
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:17,166
Very well.

15
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:19,083
You may now kiss your Amica.

16
00:01:27,583 --> 00:01:29,083
[RIKO]
I object to this ceremony!

17
00:01:29,166 --> 00:01:29,708
[RAIKA gasps]

18
00:01:29,791 --> 00:01:30,791
[KIRIN gasps]

19
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:40,583
[KIRIN yelps]

20
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:41,750
[RAIKA]
What the hell?

21
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:45,166
I'll be taking Rin-Rin with me!

22
00:01:45,250 --> 00:01:47,250
An Amica napper?

23
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:48,291
Get down!

24
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,708
What a magical day!

25
00:02:00,791 --> 00:02:03,083
The Quadra!
Isn't she awesome?

26
00:02:15,333 --> 00:02:17,375
[KIRIN screams]

27
00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:19,458
[KIRIN] Raika!
I'm being Amica-napped! Help!

28
00:02:19,541 --> 00:02:20,125
[ARIA]
Dammit!

29
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:20,791
[RAIKA]
Drop her!

30
00:02:20,875 --> 00:02:25,000
[KIRIN screams]

31
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:26,000
Gotcha!

32
00:02:26,083 --> 00:02:27,875
Say sayonara to
the mannish woman.

33
00:02:27,958 --> 00:02:29,583
I can make you much happier.

34
00:02:29,666 --> 00:02:31,708
Sure! You're so right, Riko!

35
00:02:38,708 --> 00:02:42,166
[RAIKA]
Kirin!

36
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:52,166
What a nightmare.

37
00:04:35,291 --> 00:04:36,583
[ARIA]
All right!

38
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:38,708
Let's all toast to Team Mamiya's
victory in Quartet.

39
00:04:38,791 --> 00:04:42,458
And of course, to Akari's
big promotion to D Rank!

40
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:43,791
[ALL]
Cheers!

41
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:46,458
[AKARI]
Aw, thanks so much, you guys.

42
00:04:46,541 --> 00:04:48,750
[SHINO] So you finally
made it out of E Rank.

43
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,583
Crazy, huh?

44
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:52,083
But I feel bad
that I'm the only one

45
00:04:52,166 --> 00:04:54,416
who got promoted
for our big win.

46
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
Nothin' to feel bad about.

47
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:57,041
If it wasn't for you,

48
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:58,375
we wouldn't have won
in the first place!

49
00:04:58,458 --> 00:04:59,666
Yep, that's true!

50
00:04:59,750 --> 00:05:01,166
If we were giving
medals for conduct,

51
00:05:01,250 --> 00:05:02,500
you'd have neck strain!

52
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:04,166
It wasn't just you winning.

53
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:06,208
I heard they took into
account your sportsmanship

54
00:05:06,291 --> 00:05:08,583
when you helped
Takachiho at the end.

55
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:11,875
You did a great job, Akari.
Really.

56
00:05:11,958 --> 00:05:13,416
Thank you, Aria.

57
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:16,625
[NONOKA] You must've been
scared though, huh, sis?

58
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:19,666
I mean, especially when
that scaffolding collapsed.

59
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:21,166
Yeah.

60
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:24,125
Seriously, someone should sue
that construction company.

61
00:05:24,208 --> 00:05:26,583
You guys don't think it's
possible someone actually

62
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:29,375
sabotaged that scaffold
to collapse, do you?

63
00:05:29,458 --> 00:05:30,833
[ARIA]
I'm glad you bring that up.

64
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:39,916
[ARIA] I conducted a
thorough investigation,

65
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,500
and I didn't find
anything suspicious.

66
00:05:42,583 --> 00:05:44,041
[AKARI sighs]

67
00:05:44,125 --> 00:05:44,875
Splendid!

68
00:05:44,958 --> 00:05:46,500
It was all an accident then.

69
00:05:46,583 --> 00:05:48,625
This isn't like TV where
people would do something

70
00:05:48,708 --> 00:05:51,583
completely insane to ruin a
game some girls are playing.

71
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:01,625
[NONOKA]
If it wasn't for you,

72
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:03,500
my sister would
have been killed, Reki.

73
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:05,333
Your sniping was like a miracle.

74
00:06:05,416 --> 00:06:07,750
At least, that's how she
described it back home.

75
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,250
Yeah, thanks again for
your miraculous aim.

76
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,208
I'm happy to help.

77
00:06:13,291 --> 00:06:14,666
[ARIA]
To be honest with you,

78
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,375
I had suddenly gotten a bad
gut feeling about things.

79
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:20,000
So I asked Reki to come
as an insurance policy.

80
00:06:20,083 --> 00:06:20,875
Right?

81
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:22,166
[REKI]
Yep.

82
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,416
[AKARI] Your tactical
awareness is the best!

83
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:24,833
Thanks!

84
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:27,083
Though in this case, I'm happy
my gut was proven wrong.

85
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:29,291
It's still important
that we're careful.

86
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:31,541
There are always plenty
of bad dudes out there.

87
00:06:32,958 --> 00:06:35,333
[RIKO] And a Butei
is always a target.

88
00:06:35,416 --> 00:06:36,916
Don't worry about me, Riko!

89
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,250
I've got my own personal
upperclassman watching my back!

90
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,583
[RIKO] Oh my gosh,
you are just so cute!

91
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:44,416
You make me wanna do this.

92
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:45,958
Tickle you! Come here!

93
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:47,708
--[KIRIN yells]
--[RIKO] Tickle fight!

94
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:49,250
[BOTH laughing]

95
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:50,125
Stop!

96
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:51,500
You know I don't like tickles!

97
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:52,708
[RIKO]
Tickle-tickle-tickle!

98
00:06:53,875 --> 00:06:54,958
Oh, Akari.

99
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:56,708
Uh... Yeah?

100
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,875
If your fight with
Takachiho had been real,

101
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:01,041
you would've died
when she shot you.

102
00:07:01,125 --> 00:07:02,208
[AKARI gasps]

103
00:07:02,291 --> 00:07:04,625
The first rule of
battle is to not die.

104
00:07:04,708 --> 00:07:05,750
[AKARI]
Yes, ma'am.

105
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,750
But still... Well...

106
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:10,333
A win is a win.

107
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:11,583
You did good.

108
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:15,333
Thank you for the praise!

109
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:16,833
[ARIA]
Ha!

110
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:20,833
I saw that little move
coming a mile away.

111
00:07:20,916 --> 00:07:21,916
[AKARI groans]

112
00:07:23,875 --> 00:07:25,583
She's got you beat, sis.

113
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,666
[AKARI yelling]

114
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,916
[ARIA]
You should stop,

115
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,041
before you break something
in the restaurant.

116
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,083
Gotcha!

117
00:07:41,083 --> 00:07:41,958
[AKARI gasps]

118
00:07:42,041 --> 00:07:43,416
[AKARI]
Ow, that hurt!

119
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:48,166
Mess with the bull,
you get the horns.

120
00:07:49,625 --> 00:07:50,833
[TAKACHIHO]
Ahem.

121
00:07:50,916 --> 00:07:51,875
[ALL]
Hm?

122
00:07:53,208 --> 00:07:54,833
[KIRIN]
Takachiho...

123
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:56,416
Here comes the sore loser.

124
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,041
Well, well, well.

125
00:07:58,125 --> 00:08:00,333
For a poor girl, you sure
think little of others.

126
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:01,541
What did you call me?

127
00:08:01,625 --> 00:08:03,625
Girls from Tottori
have perfect manners

128
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:05,041
and social graces.

129
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:10,125
[TAKASHIHO]
I'm here to congratulate you,

130
00:08:10,208 --> 00:08:12,708
and thank you for saving me.

131
00:08:12,791 --> 00:08:14,708
[AKARI] Thank you so much,
they're beautiful!

132
00:08:17,083 --> 00:08:18,541
Yuyu. Yaya.

133
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:19,666
We're done here.

134
00:08:22,041 --> 00:08:24,416
Even when she's trying
to be nice, she's a jerk!

135
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:25,833
We should double-check
that she hasn't

136
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,333
booby-trapped those flowers.

137
00:08:27,416 --> 00:08:28,375
Oh, come on.

138
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:30,000
She's not evil, you guys.

139
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:30,833
I'm with Shino.

140
00:08:30,916 --> 00:08:32,375
You're being too trusting.

141
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,000
Here, let me take it apart.

142
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:35,125
[AKARI]
Leave it alone!

143
00:08:35,208 --> 00:08:37,125
Why would she bring
a gift to hurt me?

144
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:38,625
[RAIKA]
Ever hear of the Trojan War?

145
00:08:38,708 --> 00:08:40,708
[AKARI] I don't want
you to ruin it! Stop!

146
00:08:43,041 --> 00:08:44,291
[RIKO]
Let's pick up where we stopped.

147
00:08:44,375 --> 00:08:45,875
Tickle fight, round two!

148
00:08:45,958 --> 00:08:47,458
Tickle-tickle, Rin-Rin, tickle!

149
00:08:47,541 --> 00:08:49,166
[KIRIN laughing]

150
00:08:49,250 --> 00:08:50,750
[RIKO]
You know you love it!

151
00:08:56,041 --> 00:08:57,750
You wanna go
somewhere else and hang?

152
00:08:57,833 --> 00:08:59,291
Yeah, I'm up for it!

153
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:01,375
Let's keep the
celebration going!

154
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,791
The reason they're happy
is because of me.

155
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:05,625
I must be a good person.

156
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:09,541
Well... You girls have fun.
I gotta jet.

157
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:11,791
No! It's still early!

158
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:13,916
[ARIA] Now, now,
you know how busy I am.

159
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:15,833
Go have fun. I mean it.

160
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:16,875
I'll be fine.

161
00:09:16,958 --> 00:09:19,750
[AKARI]
Oh, hold on! One last thing!

162
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,625
I never would
have gotten D Rank

163
00:09:21,708 --> 00:09:23,541
without the charm you gave me.

164
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:25,416
It was good luck!

165
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,416
So thank you again, Aria.

166
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,416
Uh, hey...

167
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,416
That's for preggos.

168
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,875
[ALL]
Uh...

169
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:35,416
[AKARI growls]

170
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,541
What? What's wrong?

171
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:39,083
[AKARI]
Aria gave it to me.

172
00:09:39,166 --> 00:09:42,500
So don't you make fun of it!

173
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:43,791
--[AKARI yells]
--[KINJI] I'm not!

174
00:09:43,875 --> 00:09:46,458
[KINJI] That's what it's for!
Stop it, Akari!

175
00:09:46,541 --> 00:09:47,750
[AKARI]
Get outta here!

176
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,625
All right, all right,
I'm leaving!

177
00:09:51,208 --> 00:09:52,416
[KINJI]
But just a minute.

178
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,000
Before I go...

179
00:09:54,083 --> 00:09:55,500
[AKARI]
Huh?

180
00:09:55,583 --> 00:09:58,375
I find it a little surprising
she has a friend like you.

181
00:09:58,458 --> 00:09:59,916
Since she said,

182
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,250
"I can get through this life.
Without having any friends."

183
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,000
[ARIA]
Akari!

184
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:08,291
Get back here with the girls!

185
00:10:08,375 --> 00:10:09,541
But hey...

186
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:11,166
If she's hanging with you
all the time now,

187
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,333
it frees me up
to do other stuff.

188
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:14,375
Late!

189
00:10:15,458 --> 00:10:16,500
Is something wrong?

190
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,333
Akari, I miss you!

191
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,208
We gotta keep
this party going!

192
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:21,750
[RIKO laughing]

193
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:24,708
Kii always has a way of
showing up at the wrong time.

194
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,083
Wait, who's Kii?

195
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,583
Is that like your nickname
for Kinji Tohyama?

196
00:10:28,666 --> 00:10:30,583
Yep. We keep it pretty tight.

197
00:10:30,666 --> 00:10:32,166
But don't worry.

198
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:33,625
[KIRIN yelps]

199
00:10:33,708 --> 00:10:36,208
No two people will ever be
closer than Riko and Kirin!

200
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:38,000
[RIKO]
Aw, my wittle Rin-Rin!

201
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:48,125
Is this stuff really worth
getting jealous over?

202
00:10:49,833 --> 00:10:51,208
[RIKO]
Tickle-tickle, Rin-Rin.

203
00:10:52,166 --> 00:10:53,458
[RAIKA growls]

204
00:10:53,541 --> 00:10:55,791
[yelling]

205
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:05,708
I'm... I'm reading too
much into it, aren't I?

206
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:07,208
Right? Jonathan?

207
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,250
But then...

208
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,041
Raika and Akari have
been close for a long time,

209
00:11:12,125 --> 00:11:14,666
so maybe there is something
going on there.

210
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:16,333
What am I gonna do?!

211
00:11:20,291 --> 00:11:21,708
[ARIA]
That sucks.

212
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:23,583
I really wish you had seen it.

213
00:11:23,666 --> 00:11:24,708
[HINA]
Well...

214
00:11:24,791 --> 00:11:25,875
I was fighting Raika
when it happened,

215
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:28,166
so you'll understand
my hands were full.

216
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:30,541
[ARIA] I didn't get a good
look at it myself.

217
00:11:30,625 --> 00:11:31,875
But what I do know

218
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:34,166
is she used another
strange technique.

219
00:11:37,125 --> 00:11:39,458
It was almost like a
superhero's power.

220
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:44,750
I think that falling
scaffold was...

221
00:11:44,833 --> 00:11:45,750
...a set up.

222
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,375
To force her into
using her powers

223
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:49,250
to save herself and Takachiho.

224
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:52,375
Otherwise...

225
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:54,250
It seems too convenient to me.

226
00:11:56,791 --> 00:11:59,875
I need to get to the bottom
of whatever is going on.

227
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:01,541
Can I count on you?

228
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:04,333
[HINA] Understanding what's
going on is beyond my skills.

229
00:12:04,416 --> 00:12:06,375
Have you thought about
just asking her about it?

230
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:09,208
[ARIA]
I haven't.

231
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:11,000
Maybe it's best to
just leave things be

232
00:12:11,083 --> 00:12:13,208
and hope she tells me herself.

233
00:12:13,291 --> 00:12:14,875
But that's a big
gamble, isn't it?

234
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:20,666
[RIKO]
Yeah.

235
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:23,000
I think it's best if I
lay low for a while.

236
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:25,291
Aria was also
investigating the site.

237
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:29,625
And we know the one thing she
does have is good instincts.

238
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:30,750
Having said that,

239
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,041
I don't consider her
much of a threat.

240
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:35,291
This way, you and I
can both take our time

241
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:38,416
coming up with plans and have
fun comparing them later.

242
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:39,625
[RIKO giggles]

243
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:46,125
[KINJI]
Since she said,

244
00:12:46,208 --> 00:12:49,166
"I can get through this life
without having any friends."

245
00:12:55,041 --> 00:12:56,041
Hey, Akari.

246
00:12:56,125 --> 00:12:57,208
I'm done in the bath.

247
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:58,708
Oh, great!

248
00:12:58,791 --> 00:12:59,916
That was fast.

249
00:13:02,625 --> 00:13:03,541
[AKARI gasps]

250
00:13:03,625 --> 00:13:05,125
[AKARI]
Nonoka, are you okay?

251
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:06,833
Oh, yeah, I'm fine.

252
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:08,791
I think the bath
just made me dizzy.

253
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:14,000
Well then you should
go to bed right now.

254
00:13:18,083 --> 00:13:19,708
[NONOKA]
What's going on?

255
00:13:19,791 --> 00:13:22,125
Lately, I've been feeling
a little strange.

256
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:33,375
